start: Chapter2CommandersReport

title: Chapter2CommandersReport
position: -423,-35
---
Night hangs over the camp as commanders crowd around the war table.
Reports of enemy movements pile up, each more urgent than the last.
You can wait for the scouts to return, or make your decision now.

[[Wait for the scouts' report before committing to an attack.|Chapter2ScoutReport]]
<<jump Chapter2ScoutReport>>
[[Decide now, without waiting for more information.|Chapter2SonLeadsChargeDecision]]
<<jump Chapter2SonLeadsChargeDecision>>
===

title: Chapter2ScoutReport
position: 192,-233
---
Mud-streaked scouts burst into the tent, breathless.
"Their main force is forming up on the ridge," one gasps.
"If we strike before dawn, we might catch them unprepared."

[[Return to the war council and decide who will lead the attack.|Chapter2SonLeadsChargeDecision]]
<<jump Chapter2SonLeadsChargeDecision>>
===

title: Chapter2SonLeadsChargeDecision
position: -63,318
---
Your son steps forward, eyes burning with determination.
"Father, let me lead the charge. Our men will rally if they see me at the front."
The war council falls silent, all eyes on you.

[[Allow your son to lead the charge.|Chapter2AllowOutcome]]
<<jump Chapter2AllowOutcome>>
[[Deny your son and lead the charge yourself.|Chapter2DenyOutcome]]
<<jump Chapter2DenyOutcome>>
===

title: Chapter2AllowOutcome
position: 455,190
---
The banners rise and your son rides at the front.
The charge shatters the enemy line, but when the dust settles, his banner lies torn in the mud.
Your son is dead, and victory tastes like ash.
===

title: Chapter2DenyOutcome
position: 384,-61
---
You place a hand on his shoulder. "No. I will lead them."
His jaw tightens, but he steps back as you ride out.
The men hesitate; the charge falters. By dusk, the field is lost and your banners burn on the horizon.
===
